                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn1" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>kipliklerin</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn2" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>synyqlyqlardan birkinediler</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">מִשְּׁבָרִ֗ים
                                יִתְחַטָּאוּ </foreign>
                             ‘because of his crashings they are beside themselves’ (Job 41:25); see
                            next footnote.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn3" type="footnote">A second alternative translation
                            to <emph>synyqlyqlardan birkinediler</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">מִשְּׁבָרִ֗ים
                                יִתְחַטָּאוּ </foreign>
                             ‘because of his crashings they are beside themselves’ (Job
                            41:25).</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn4" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>oporoq taslar</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign
                                xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">אַבְנֵי־קָלַע </foreign>
                             ‘slingstones’ (Job 41:28).</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn5" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>anyn tibine iti taslar tegenekler kibik</emph>, the equivalent
                            of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">תַּחְתָּיו
                                חַדּוּדֵי חָרֶשׂ </foreign>
                             ‘his underparts are like sharp potsherds’ (Job 41:30).</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn6" type="footnote">Spelled <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">ײַרַטִילְגַנְאדִי</foreign>
                             ; a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-041-fn7" type="footnote">In the standard Hebrew Bible, Job
                            42 begins here.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
